```


## tests

The NetCDF test fixtures are tracked with Git LFS. After cloning this
repository, install/pull the LFS objects before configuring tests:

```sh
git lfs install
git lfs pull
```

When the build is configured with `-DCODEX_USE_VISKORES=ON`, CMake adds Viskores
CTest tests. The generate tests run the compact puncture path and create combined
text files with all punctures:

```sh
cd build-viskores2
make test
```

Useful direct commands:

```sh
ctest -R viskores_generate --output-on-failure
ctest -R viskores_compare --output-on-failure
ctest -R viskores_mpi --output-on-failure
ctest -R 'viskores_mpi_compare_.*_serial' --output-on-failure
```

Generated combined puncture files are written under the build tree:

```text
build-viskores2/test-output/viskores_generate_single_text/ip_cxx.single.all.txt
build-viskores2/test-output/viskores_generate_circ_text/ip_cxx.circ.all.txt
build-viskores2/test-output/viskores_mpi_generate_single_text/ip_cxx.single.all.txt
build-viskores2/test-output/viskores_mpi_generate_circ_text/ip_cxx.circ.all.txt
build-viskores2/test-output/viskores_mpi_compare_single_serial/mpi/ip_cxx.single.all.txt
build-viskores2/test-output/viskores_mpi_compare_circ_serial/mpi/ip_cxx.circ.all.txt
```

The MATLAB comparison tests compare Viskores puncture output against the
`data/zperiod_5` MATLAB reference files and print row counts plus max XYZ error.
Those comparison tests may fail while the Viskores/MATLAB mismatch is being
debugged.

When configured with `-DCODEX_USE_MPI=ON`, CMake also adds 2-rank MPI versions
of the same generation and MATLAB comparison tests. It also adds MPI-vs-serial
tests that compare each MPI puncture file against a serial Viskores run for the
same line list. Override the rank count with:

```sh
cmake -S . -B build-viskores2 -DCODEX_TEST_MPI_PROCS=4
```

Test data paths can be overridden at configure time:

```sh
cmake -S . -B build-viskores2 \
  -DCODEX_USE_VISKORES=ON \
  -DCODEX_TEST_DATA_DIR=/path/to/test-data
```

